🔷 2.1 Data Preprocessing (Cleaning the data)

👉 Before training any model, data must be cleaned and prepared.

Think:

Bad data → Bad model
Good data → Good model
✅ 1. Handling Missing Data

Sometimes data has missing values:

Age	Salary
25	40k
30	❌
👉 df.fillna()
df.fillna(0)

✔ Replaces missing values with something (like 0 or mean)

Example:

Missing salary → replace with average salary
👉 df.dropna()
df.dropna()

✔ Removes rows with missing values

Use when:

Too many missing values → better to remove row
✅ 2. Encoding Categorical Data

Models understand numbers, not text.

Example:

Gender
Male
Female
👉 pd.get_dummies()
pd.get_dummies(df)

✔ Converts into columns:

Male	Female
1	0
0	1
👉 LabelEncoder()
Male → 0
Female → 1

✔ Converts text into numbers

✅ 3. Feature Scaling

👉 Important when features have different ranges

Example:

Age	Salary
25	50000

Salary is much bigger → model becomes biased.

🔹 Standardization
(x - mean) / std

👉 Makes data centered around 0

Tool:

StandardScaler()
🔹 Normalization
(x - min) / (max - min)

👉 Converts values between 0 and 1

Tool:

MinMaxScaler()
✅ 4. Splitting Data
train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.2)

👉 Split data into:

80% → training
20% → testing

✔ Train on one part
✔ Test on unseen data

🔷 2.2 Model Evaluation Metrics

👉 These tell how good your model is

✅ Regression Metrics (for numbers)
1. MSE (Mean Squared Error)
(predicted - actual)^2

✔ Penalizes large errors more

2. RMSE
√MSE

✔ Easier to understand (same unit as output)

3. MAE (Mean Absolute Error)
|predicted - actual|

✔ Simple average error

4. R² Score
How well model explains data (0 to 1)

✔ 1 → perfect
✔ 0 → bad

✅ Classification Metrics (for categories)
1. Accuracy
Correct predictions / Total
2. Precision
Out of predicted YES → how many correct?
3. Recall
Out of actual YES → how many found?
4. F1 Score
Balance of precision & recall
5. ROC-AUC

👉 Measures how well model separates classes

✅ Cross Validation
cross_val_score(model, X, y, cv=5)

👉 Split data into 5 parts

Train on 4 parts
Test on 1 part
Repeat 5 times

✔ Gives more reliable performance

